{"lemma": "عِمارَةٌ", "slug": "عِمارَةٌ", "root": "ع.م.ر", "root_slug": "ع-م-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-م-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "عِمارَة", "root": "عمر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 5}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n30530", "n30531", "n30532"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "building", "fa": "ساختمان", "ur": "عمارت", "tr": "bina", "id": "bangunan", "bn": "ভবন", "es": "construcción", "fr": "construction", "de": "Gebäude", "ru": "строительство", "zh": "建筑"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of عَمُرَ (ʕamura) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of عَمَرَ (ʕamara) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "tribe, clan"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of عَمَرَ (ʕamara) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "building, structure"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n30530", "headword_ar": "عَمَارَةٌ", "root": "Emr", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AO, S, O, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which one puts,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which a chief puts,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon his head, such as a turban,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalanosuwap", "text_ar": "قَلَنْسُوَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a crown, &c.,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AO, S, O, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as a sign of headship, and for keeping it in mind;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamorapN", "text_ar": "عَمْرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArN", "text_ar": "عَمَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O, * TA:) which last [is app. a coll. gen. n., of which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArapN", "text_ar": "عَمَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the n. un., and] also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any sweet-smelling plant"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rayoHaAn", "text_ar": "رَيْحَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which a chief puts upon his head for the same purpose:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and hence, (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any such plant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "absolutely: (B:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any such plant with which a drinkingchamber is adorned,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "called by the Persians"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mayowaraAno", "text_ar": "مَيْوَرَانْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when any one comes in to the people there assembled, they raise somewhat thereof with their hands, and salute him with it, wishing him a long life:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so, accord. to some, in a verse of El-Aashà, which see below: (S:) or it there signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "crowns of such plants, which they put upon their heads, as the foreigners"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEajam", "text_ar": "العَجَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "do;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but ISd says, “ I know not how this is: ” or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "myrtle;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=s", "text_ar": "ا=س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArpN", "text_ar": "عَمَارةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a plant of that kind, with which one used to salute a king, saying, May God prolong thy life:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a raising of the voice, saying so:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az, TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a salutation;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) said to mean,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God prolong thy life;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArN", "text_ar": "عَمَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EimaArapN", "text_ar": "عِمَارَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (L;) but Az says that this explanation is not valid. (TA.) El-Aashà says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "falam~aA A^ataAnaA buEayoda AlkaraY\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      sajadonaA lahu warafaEonaA AlEamaAraA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And when he came to us, a little after slumber, we prostrated ourselves to him, and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "we put the turbans from our heads,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in honour of him: (S:) but IB says that, accord. to this explanation, the correct reading is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waDaEonaA AlEamaAraA", "text_ar": "وَضَعْنَا العَمَارَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) or the former reading means,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "we raised our voices with prayer for him, and said, May God prolong thy life:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "we raised the sweet-smelling plants: &c.:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see above. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArapN", "text_ar": "عَمَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EimaArapN", "text_ar": "عِمَارَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An ornamented piece of cloth which is sewed upon a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "miZ~l~ap", "text_ar": "مِظّلَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [by which is meant"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a kind of tent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (O, K, TA,) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sewed to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tariyqap", "text_ar": "طَرِيقَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on each side of the tent-pole,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as a sign of headship."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EimaArapN", "text_ar": "عِمَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["AO", "S", "O", "K", "TA", "B", "Az"]}, {"entry_id": "n30531", "headword_ar": "عُمَارَةٌ", "root": "Emr", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Hire, pay,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wages, of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EimaArap", "text_ar": "عِمَارَة"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as signifying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA yuEomaru bihi AlmakaAnu", "text_ar": "مَا يُعْمَرُ بِهِ المَكَانُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[see below]. (K, TA.)"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n30532", "headword_ar": "عِمَارَةٌ", "root": "Emr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[is an inf. n.: and often signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Habitation and cultivation;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a good state of habitation and cultivation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "―         -b2-  and is also expl. as signifying]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA yuEomaru bihi AlmakaAnu", "text_ar": "مَا يُعْمَرُ بِهِ المَكَانُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That by which a place is rendered inhabited, peopled, well stocked with people and the like, colonized, cultivated, well cultivated, in a flourishing state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in a state the contrary of desolate"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "waste"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ruined;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "app. meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "work,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "labour, by which a place is rendered so;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as it is immediately added in the K that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EumaArapN", "text_ar": "عُمَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies hire, pay, or wages, of it, or for it; and the explanation which I have here given is agreeable with ancient and modern usage; to which it may be further added, that the measure ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiEaAlapN", "text_ar": "فِعَالَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") is common to words signifying arts, occupations, or employments, as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziraAEapN", "text_ar": "زِرَاعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "filaAHapN", "text_ar": "فِلَاحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]. (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also a subst. from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eamara Ald~aAra", "text_ar": "عَمَرَ الدَّارَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) [It has two significations, either of which may be meant in the Msb: The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "act,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "art, of building"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a house: ―         -b4-  and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A building; a structure; an edifice:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "generally, accord. to modern usage,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a public edifice:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaAy^iru", "text_ar": "عَمَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EumoraAnN", "text_ar": "عُمْرَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]       -A2-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "breast"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EimaArapN", "text_ar": "عِمَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArapN", "text_ar": "عَمَارَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K,) the latter allowed by Kh, (O,) but the former is the more common, (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A great tribe,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qibiylapN EaZiymapN", "text_ar": "قِبِيلَةٌ عَظِيمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaY~N EaZiymN", "text_ar": "حَىٌّ عَظِيمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that subsists by itself, migrating by itself, and abiding by itself, and seeking pasturage by itself:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, TA:) or it is called by the former name because it peoples a land; and by the latter, because complex like a turban; (TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamiyrapN", "text_ar": "عَمِيرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the same; or, as some say, all signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baTon", "text_ar": "بَطْن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Ham p. 682:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qabiylapN", "text_ar": "قَبِيلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ea$iyrapN", "text_ar": "عَشِيرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "less than a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qbylp", "text_ar": "قبيلة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "less than a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qbylp", "text_ar": "قبيلة"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and more than a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baTon", "text_ar": "بَطْن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (IAth, TA:) [see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aEobN", "text_ar": "شَعْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a body of men by which a place is peopled:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(B, TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaAy^iru", "text_ar": "عَمَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)       -A3-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EamaArapN", "text_ar": "عَمَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places."}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "O", "Msb", "K", "IAth", "B"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}